caseText:"<p>Royal Tea Limited manufactures and distributes finest quality black tea to hotels, restaurants and retailers. The company has wide presence in tea market. It has become one of the largest premium brands. The customers are very happy with the finest quality of tea.</p> <p>Royal Tea Limited never compromises with the quality of the tea. The aim of the company is to deliver finest black tea to keep the customers happy. Instead of sourcing from the open market, RTL has tied up with big tea estates for procurement of finest tea leaves directly from the estate for processing in its own plants. The tea leaves go through various processes like plucking, withering, brushing, oxidizing, grading, drying, sorting and shaping etc. Then these are packed in jars for distribution to the hotels, restaurants and retailers.</p> <p>A growing market for beverages like tea has increased the number of tea manufacturers, thereby increasing competition in the industry. Although their tea is not of the same superior quality as RTL&rsquo;s, many manufacturers offer their tea at low prices to gain market share. Buckling to peer pressure tactics, RTL&rsquo;s management has also decided to reduce the price per kilogram of tea to match average market prices. The aim of this price reduction is to increase the volume of sales by making their product appealing to the mass market in particular the retail and street shops. Higher volumes would contribute to growth of profits. RTL has purchased prime TV time slots in order to reach out to the mass market and advertise its products.</p> <p>Prices of tea leaves has been fluctuating in the past few months. The rest of the parameters like standard hours required for production of 1 kilogram tea, standard labour rates are expected to be stable, other than increased advertising expenses, which can be predicted accurately, other fixed overhead costs are expected to be stable. In April 2026, newer budget standards were finalized based on the recent management decisions and expected fluctuations in market prices.</p> <p>The following variances were compiled in May 2026, pertain to last month's operations that arose as a consequence of implementation of above decisions and revised budget standards:</p> <table> <tbody> <tr> <td>Sales Price Variance</td> <td>2,40,500 (A)</td> </tr> <tr> <td>Sales Volume Variance</td> <td>2,00,600 (F)</td> </tr> <tr> <td>Material Price Variance</td> <td>1,50,500 (A)</td> </tr> <tr> <td>Labour Efficiency Variance</td> <td>1,40,300 (A)</td> </tr> <tr> <td>Fixed Cost Expenditure Variance</td> <td>1,10,100 (A)</td> </tr> </tbody> </table> <p>On receiving the above information in the MIS report, the management has decided to revise its product pricing strategy yet again. Keeping in mind the nature of its tea, it decided to do a sensitivity analysis to understand customer behavior. </p>",    
